British ColumbiaResources Investment Corp said it successfully concludedrefinancing negotiations with bankers for a new 360 mln dlrrestructured credit facility.    The credit line will be in place for four years to March31, 1991, but is extendable up to 10 years under certaincircumstances which were not specified by the company.    B.C. Resources said subsidiaries Westar Timber and WestarPetroleum have settled revised lending agreements, but debtdiscussions regarding subsidiary Westar Mining are continuing. Reuter&#3;